div.p:
The time being come, that we were to goe fetch the Sogdian Princes, I went to take leave of Senira, and then communicated the plot I had laid to pring up ome occaion of contet with Zadarem, whoe ill contrived behaviour promis'd me ubject enough. He condicended, in fine, to let me lay hold of fortunes foretep to free my elf from my Geroe, and aured me of the honour of his protection and power on al occaions,
or accidents, and withall to give order in my abence for my nerias liberty, which he oon after nobly procured. No ooner were we arrived in Sogdiana, and had paid our civility to the Princes, who was indeed rich both in beauty and vertue, but Zadarem began amongt the praies he howred upon her, to let fall ome drops of Mediance and lander upon Themira's reputation: he went every where proclaiming that the Prince needed not o much regret her los, ince the chater flames this worthy Lady might kindle in his heart, could not but extinguih thoe lighter fancies and carees of a Mitris. This malice was o apparent that every one reented it as very candalous, there was not any in our company that was not well acquainted with the fair Themira's unoyl'd vertue, and had valour and will enough to aert it; but they all flung their looks on me, who am allyed to her, expecting I hould ty up his inolent tongue from bepattering her with uch abues. One day after I had mildly reproved him, he had the impudence to ask me, whether the Prince had o far loved me, as to let me hare with him in that gentle fortune, ince I took upon me to vindicate him; and if o, that he had yet o much dicretion left in tock, as not to wake his iters jealouy with the report of it; and when I reply'd, that I had no farther interet in her, but only what every Gentleman would be oblig'd to for his kindred, to preerve their reputation, which therefore engaged me not to hear a peron of her high worth o unhandomely calumniated;
he promis'd me, but in a kind of raillery, that ince it concerned me o neerly, he would be very careful hereafter not to let fly any thing that might call up my anger: which nevertheles he did not oberve; He could not retrain his itching tongue from publihing a hundred wanton Tales, and noied the reentment I had hown, which I was forc'd to pocket up till we were returned into Margiana, as unwilling to violate that repect we owe to tranger Countries.
